[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in court charged with raping woman in Paisley

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has appeared in court charged with raping a woman as she walked home in Renfrewshire at the weekend.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Stanislaw Merdacz, 38, is accused of attacking the 40-year-old in Paisley at about 02:20 on Sunday.
Prosecutors claim the attack took place on a grassed area at the junction of Shortroods Road and Mosslands Road.
At Paisley Sheriff Court, Mr Merdacz, who is originally from Poland, made made no plea or declaration and was remanded in custody.
Mr Merdacz is accused of grabbing the woman, forcing her to the ground, punching her on her head and clamping his hand over her mouth.
He is then said to have pulled off her lower clothing, pulled rings from her fingers and raped her.
